LanternOS Licensing
===================

This is a multi-licence project.

Code
----
Unless a repository or file states otherwise, source code in LanternOS is dual-licensed
under either of:

  * Apache License, Version 2.0 (see LICENSE-APACHE)
  * MIT license (see LICENSE-MIT)

at your option. This is the conventional dual-licensing scheme of the Rust ecosystem and
maximises downstream compatibility.

Some firmware/kernel components may additionally be offered under a different licence
where required for hardware ecosystem compatibility; such exceptions are stated in the
relevant repository's own LICENSE file and tracked via ADR.

Documentation
-------------
Documentation, including the contents of lantern-docs and all wiki/, ARCHITECTURE.md,
THREAT_MODEL.md and RFC files, is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International License (CC BY 4.0). See LICENSE-DOCS.

Contributions
-------------
Unless you explicitly state otherwise, any contribution intentionally submitted for
inclusion in the work by you shall be licensed as above, without any additional terms or
conditions. Contributors should include a Signed-off-by line (DCO 1.1) on commits.
